TV presenter and former Metro FM radio host, Thembisa Mdoda is booked and busy! The actress has bagged herself a new role on hit show Isibaya. She will star as Amanda, a high-level corporate woman in her late 30s, very successful and an executive for a Sandton based asset management company. Mdoda is currently working on BET’s new wedding show READ: THEMBISA MDODA TO HOST NEW WEDDING SHOW! She will make her first appearance on the show on Friday, 19 July arriving to collect Malaika from Phumelele, played by Ayanda Borotho. 